Rating: 4
Like another reviewer, I opted to do this in the crockpot with beef chuck (i.e., grocery store "beef for stew"). I browned the meat in olive oil, threw in shallots and carrots and cooked for 3 minutes. Then I added spices and stock (left out cayenne for sake of my 3 kids) and brought to full pressure for 40 minutes. The result was fantastic with mint and a generous squeeze of lemon juice, served over couscous. Everyone loved it.

