Rating: 4
This was excellent, and even my fussy kids liked it! I will admit I used a cheaper cut of meat and a pressure cooker to save money without spending a lot more time. I just browned the meat first, then the shallots, added the spices, then poured in the broth and cooked it at full pressure for 10 min. Cooled it quickly, added the carrots and cooked at pressure for 5 min., then cooled it quickly, thickened the sauce and seasoned with salt, pepper and mint. Since stew meat is already cut up, it took no more time than the original version. Delicious!

